## Description
The **Deliver Files (FTP) **task allows to deliver files via (S)FTP.

> Note

When delivering files via (S)FTP, if needed, the system performs a number of retries depending on the general configuration settings.

## Configuration
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- Click on the **Endpoint &gt; Resource **field and select the FTP Endpoint resource to use.

> Note

For more information, see: [FTP Endpoint Resource Reference](/doxee-platform/docs/ftp-endpoint-resource-reference).

- *(optional) *Enable the **Use temporary files **option to save partial files to the FTP server using a temporary suffix.

> Note

The temporary suffix will be automatically removed and the file will be saved using the correct extension when the file transfer is complete.

- *(optional) *Enable the **Use semaphore files **option to create a semaphore file for each output file.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Configure the required parameters:

**Field**

**Description**

**Semaphore name**

Select the required option to define the name of the semaphore file:

**Base name**: the output file's full name without its extension

- **Full name**: the output file's full name including its extension

**Semaphore extension**

*(optional) *Enter a custom extension to be appended to the name of the semaphore file.

> Note

The extension is not mandatory; if not configured, the semaphore file name will be the name of the output file, as configured in the **Semaphore name **field.

> Note

Semaphore files are created only after all files have been transferred.

- In the **Output **section, fill in the required fields:

Enable the **LOTXML **option to define the FTP path dynamically.

> Note

If this option is enabled, the **Folder **and **Pattern **fields below are automatically hidden.

> Note

The delivery channel option file (usually referred to as LOTXML) is an XML file produced by a DC task that contains metadata information describing the materials to be delivered.

For more information on the legacy DP2 Multichannel Distribution LOTXML specification, see: 

[MD Delivery Channel Option File (LOTXML) Specification](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/MD%2BDelivery%2BChannel%2BOption%2BFile%2B%28LOTXML%29%2BSpecification)

[LOTXML FTP Gateway](https://code.doxee.com/confluence/display/DD/LOTXML%2BFTP%2BGateway)

- Manually specify the FTP destination folder and output filename pattern:

Enter the name of the destination **Folder **on the FTP server.

- *(optional) *Enter the filename **Pattern **in glob format to filter the files to send (for example: **.zip*).

> Tip

To match multiple file extensions (for example: csv, txt, xml) you can use the following syntax:

`*.{csv,txt,xml}`
